This is a simple implementation of a live Twitter tracker. It uses node.js + WebSockets + Twitter Streaming API to push tweets onto a page in realtime. See it live at http://tylor.no.de

To get started: 
- install node.js: http://nodejs.org/
- install the npm package manager: https://github.com/isaacs/npm#readme
- install express, socket.io, and twitter-node:
  - 'npm install express'
  - 'npm install socket.io'
  - 'npm install twitter-node' 
- clone the repository with 'git clone git://github.com/tylor/nutella.git'.
- move into the directory 'cd nutella'.
- since this is a branch right now, switch: 'git checkout express'
- enter your Twitter credentials in server.js.
- start server by running 'node server.js'.
- open a browser at http://localhost:3000 and see the magic.

This builds on the work of others, check out and support their work:
- http://expressjs.com/
- http://socket.io/
- https://github.com/technoweenie/twitter-node
